clusterdata.sources

Class TaskEventSource

  • java.lang.Object
    • clusterdata.sources.TaskEventSource
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, org.apache.flink.api.common.functions.Function, org.apache.flink.streaming.api.functions.source.SourceFunction<TaskEvent>

    public class TaskEventSource
extends Object
implements org.apache.flink.streaming.api.functions.source.SourceFunction<TaskEvent>
    This SourceFunction generates a data stream of TaskEvent records which are read from a gzipped input file. Each record has a time stamp and the input file must be ordered by this time stamp. In order to simulate a realistic stream source, the SourceFunction serves events proportional to their timestamps. In addition, the serving of events can be delayed by a bounded random delay which causes the events to be served slightly out-of-order of their timestamps. The serving speed of the SourceFunction can be adjusted by a serving speed factor. A factor of 60.0 increases the logical serving time by a factor of 60, i.e., events of one minute (60 seconds) are served in 1 second. This SourceFunction is an EventSourceFunction and does continuously emit watermarks. Hence it is able to operate in event time mode which is configured as follows: StreamExecutionEnvironment.setStreamTimeCharacteristic(TimeCharacteristic.EventTime)

        public TaskEventSource(String dataFilePath,
                       int servingSpeedFactor)
        Serves the TaskEvent records from the specified and ordered gzipped input file. Events are served exactly in order of their time stamps in a serving speed which is proportional to the specified serving speed factor.

      • TaskEventSource

        public TaskEventSource(String dataFilePath,
                       int maxEventDelaySecs,
                       int servingSpeedFactor)
        Serves the TaskEvent records from the specified and ordered gzipped input file. Events are served out-of time stamp order with specified maximum random delay in a serving speed which is proportional to the specified serving speed factor.
        Parameters:
        dataFilePath - The gzipped input file from which the TaskEvent records are read.
        maxEventDelaySecs - The max time in seconds by which events are delayed.
        servingSpeedFactor - The serving speed factor by which the logical serving time is adjusted.
